00040 ///
00041 /// Interface for MSData analyzers.
00042 ///
00043 /// MSDataAnalyzer encapsulates a passive update strategy.  The MSDataAnalyzer expects to  
00044 /// handle events generated from an outside driver.  This allows the driver to 
00045 /// control access to the MSData object -- in particular, the driver can ensure
00046 /// that scans are read from file only once.
00047 ///
00048 /// Event sequence: 
00049 ///   - open
00050 ///   - loop: 
00051 ///     - updateReqested
00052 ///     - update
00053 ///   - close
00054 ///
00055 /// UpdateRequest_Ok handles the following use case: a spectrum cache wants to cache 
00056 /// only those spectra that are requested by other MSDataAnalyzers; it won't request 
00057 /// any updates, but it needs to see any update requested by someone else.
00058 ///
00059 class PWIZ_API_DECL MSDataAnalyzer
00060 {
00061     public:
00062 
00063     /// information about the data to be analyzed
00064     struct PWIZ_API_DECL DataInfo
00065     {
00066         const MSData& msd;
00067         std::string sourceFilename;
00068         std::string outputDirectory;
00069         std::ostream* log;
00070 
00071         DataInfo(const MSData& _msd) : msd(_msd), log(0) {}
00072     };
00073 
00074     enum PWIZ_API_DECL UpdateRequest
00075     {
00076         UpdateRequest_None,      // do not update
00077         UpdateRequest_Ok,        // will accept an update
00078         UpdateRequest_NoBinary,  // update requested, no binary data needed 
00079         UpdateRequest_Full       // update requested, with binary data 
00080     };
00081 
00082     /// \name Event Handling 
00083     //@{
00084 
00085     /// start analysis of the data
00086     virtual void open(const DataInfo& dataInfo) {}
00087 
00088     /// ask analyzer if it wants an update
00089     virtual UpdateRequest updateRequested(const DataInfo& dataInfo,
00090                                           const SpectrumIdentity& spectrumIdentity) const 
00091     {   
00092         return UpdateRequest_None;
00093     }
00094 
00095     /// analyze a single spectrum
00096     virtual void update(const DataInfo& dataInfo, 
00097                         const Spectrum& spectrum) {}
00098 
00099     /// end analysis of the data
00100     virtual void close(const DataInfo& dataInfo) {} 
00101     //@}
00102 
00103     virtual ~MSDataAnalyzer() {}
00104 };

00110 /// This auxilliary class should be specialized for MSDataAnalyzers
00111 /// whose instantiation is controlled by user-supplied strings 
00112 /// (via command line, config file, etc.).

00115 {

00117     static const char* id() {return "analyzer_traits not specialized";}
00118 
00119     /// description of the analyzer
00120     static const char* description() {return typeid(analyzer_type).name();} 
00121 
00122     /// format of args string
00123     static const char* argsFormat() {return "";}
00124

00127 };

00164

00167     {
00168         public:
